  "prompt": "What are philosophical quotes?",
  "response": "Philosophical quotes are succinct expressions of wisdom or reflections on fundamental questions and ideas related to existence, knowledge, values, reason, mind, and language. These quotes are often derived from the writings and teachings of philosophers and thinkers through the ages. They aim to provoke thought, offer insights, and inspire contemplation about the nature of reality and human experience. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. \u201cThe unexamined life is not worth living.\u201d \u2013 Socrates\n2. \u201cI think, therefore I am.\u201d \u2013 Ren\u00e9 Descartes\n3. \u201cTo be is to be perceived.\u201d \u2013 George Berkeley\n4. \u201cHappiness is not an ideal of reason but of imagination.\u201d \u2013 Immanuel Kant\n5. \u201cMan is condemned to be free.\u201d \u2013 Jean-Paul Sartre\n6. \u201cIn individuals, insanity is rare; but in groups, parties, nations, and epochs, it is the rule.\u201d \u2013 Friedrich Nietzsche\n7. \u201cThe only thing I know is that I know nothing.\u201d \u2013 Socrates\n\nThese quotes capture the essence of philosophical inquiry, encouraging deeper exploration and understanding of life's most profound questions.",
